<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1197">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/189.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Stadden</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Manzanillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A new law imposing a war tax of six per cent on assessed value of
                            property has been enacted by the Colima legislature. Please instruct if
                            protest should be made as your January 21<note n="101" xml:id="d1197fn101">Printed under Forced Loans, <ref target="#pg_770">p. 770</ref>.</note> instructs on forced
                            loans.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stadden</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>